ants, in the sense that small\nmismatches in the equality constraints do not compromise the closed-loop\nstability; but a direct IOP implementation will fail to stabilize open-loop\nunstable systems in practice. The SLP is known to enjoy numerical robustness in\nthe state feedback case; here, we show that numerical robustness of the\nfour-block SLP controller requires case-by-case analysis even the plant is\nopen-loop stable.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Sep 2019 19:18:18 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 May 2020 18:02:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 4 Feb 2022 17:19:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-16"}
