y if not all Be stars have close companions influencing their\nouter disks. If confirmed to be subdwarf companions, the mass transfer spin-up\nscenario might explain the existence of the vast majority of classical Be\nstars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 26 Sep 2019 22:04:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Dec 2019 20:56:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-12-20"}
